			<div class="content" id="post-content-4404508">
									

<p>This article is literally just swamp thing from DC comics but without character development.</p>
<p>The writer tried to make it scary in the end of the article by saying it killed people and all and it looks rushed, like he wrote the article about a sentient tumbleweed and in the end he asked himself why would anyone care and decided that the thing that only eats dead plant matter now kills people.</p>
<p>And the sentences like: &quot;In terms of behavior, SCP-615 is no different from any other territorial organism. It will commonly patrol a several square mile area and will aggressively attack anything that attempts to intrude into its territory&quot; are horribly vague and uncientific, the only predator that I can think that behaves in this way are humans, we kill everything, but most other animals will continue living, move, or if hungry and carnivorous try to attack. But my point is not the behaviour but the vagueness</p>

